snippet: A day after a leading opposition figure was assassinated, Tunisia’s dominant party said it opposed a plan to dissolve the government, according to news reports.
abstract: Tunisia's governing Islamist-led party rejects proposal by Prime Min Hamadi Jebali to form government of national unity, deepening country's political crisis day after opposition leader Chokri Belaid was killed outside his home.

byline.original: By KAREEM FAHIM and DAVID D. KIRKPATRICK
byline.contributor: Kareem Fahim reported from Tunis, and David D. Kirkpatrick from Antakya, Turkey. Monica Marks contributed reporting from Tunis, Alan Cowell from Paris, and Rick Gladstone from New York.

lead_paragraph: A day after a leading opposition figure was assassinated, Tunisia’s dominant party said it opposed a plan to dissolve the government, according to news reports.

headline.seo: New Political Uncertainty Grips Tunisia After Assassination
